{{use dmy dates|date=July 2016}} {{use list-defined references|date=July 2016}} {{Use British English|date=July 2016}} {{Infobox university |name = Domus Academy |native_name = |latin_name = |logo = DomusAcademy LOGO.tif |image_size = |caption = |motto = |established = 1982 |type = Private school |president = |principal = |dean = | head_label = | head = |postgrad = | campus = {{unbulleted list|via Carlo Darwin 20|20143 Milan}} | coor = {{coord|45.4456|9.1744|display=inline,title}} |doctoral = |city = Milan |country = Italy |website = {{URL|domusacademy.com}} }}
'''Domus Academy''' is a private school of design in [[Milan, Italy]]. It offers post-graduate and professional courses in fashion, [[industrial design]], and [[design management]].{{r|nonaka|page=132}} It is not listed by the [[Ministero dell'Istruzione, dell'Università e della Ricerca]], the Italian ministry of education, among the institutions authorised to award degrees in music, dance and the arts.{{r|miur}}
Domus Academy was founded in 1982 by the Mazzocchi family, owners of {{Interlanguage link multi|Editoriale Domus|it}}, which publishes [[Domus (magazine)|''Domus'']] and ''[[Quattroruote]]'' magazines.{{r|rep}} Maria Grazia Mazzocchi was president of the school.{{r|rep}} [[Gianfranco Ferré]] was on the staff from 1983 to 1989,{{r|alfonsi|san}} and [[Andrea Branzi]] was cultural director for the first ten years.{{r|rep}} In 2009 the school was bought by [[Laureate Education]] of [[Baltimore, Maryland]] for an estimated ten million euros.{{r|rep}} In 2018 Laureate sold it to the British [[Galileo Global Education]] group.{{r|sole}}
